   "id": "cell-sec2-title",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "---\n",
    "## 2. Directed vs. Undirected Graphs\n",
    "\n",
    "On **Facebook**, friendship goes both ways — if Alice is friends with Bob, Bob is also friends with Alice. That's an *undirected* graph.\n",
    "\n",
    "On **Twitter/X**, you can follow someone without them following you back. That's a *directed* graph — edges have arrows."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 7,
   "id": "cell-digraph",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Is directed? True\n",
      "\n",
      "Alice: in-degree=3, out-degree=1\n",
      "Bob: in-degree=2, out-degree=1\n",
      "Carol: in-degree=0, out-degree=2\n",
      "Dave: in-degree=0, out-degree=1\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# A directed \"follows\" graph — edges have direction (A → B ≠ B → A)\n",
    "D = nx.DiGraph()\n",
    "D.add_edge(\"Alice\", \"Bob\")  # Alice follows Bob\n",
    "D.add_edge(\"Bob\", \"Alice\")  # Bob follows back (mutual)\n",
    "D.add_edge(\"Carol\", \"Alice\")  # Carol follows Alice (one-way)\n",
    "D.add_edge(\"Carol\", \"Bob\")\n",
    "D.add_edge(\"Dave\", \"Alice\")\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"Is directed?\", D.is_directed())\n",
    "print()\n",
    "\n",
    "# In directed graphs every node has an in-degree AND an out-degree\n",
    "for node in D.nodes():\n",
    "    print(f\"{node}: in-degree={D.in_degree(node)}, out-degree={D.out_degree(node)}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 8,
   "id": "cell-draw-digraph",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
